Cases are rising fast in Africa, but deaths remain steady. AFP/Zinyange Auntony JOHANNESBURG - 3,049 new COVID-19 infections have been recorded in the last 24 hours. Less than a thousand new cases were reported in each province. READ: Covid-19 vaccines showed high efficacy against severe Omicron: US data Gauteng continues to lead with 774 new cases. It is followed by the Western Cape with 580. KwaZulu-Natal is third with 462. The positivity rate stands at 9.2 percent. A further 13 deaths have been reported, taking the death toll to nearly 95,000. #COVID19 UPDATE: 33,117 tests were conducted in the last 24hrs, with 3,049 new cases, representing a 9.2% positivity rate. 13 #COVID19 related deaths have been reported in the last 24-48hrs, total fatalities amount to 94,063 to date. See more here: https://t.co/K2yGVc2zNi pic.twitter.com/9RKVBAvnKf